===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|hevy}}, {{m|enm|heviȝ}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|hefiġ}}, {{m|ang|hefeġ}}, {{m|ang|hæfiġ||heavy; important, grave, severe, serious; oppressive, grievous; slow, dull}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*habīgaz||heavy, hefty, weighty}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*keh₂p-||to take, grasp, hold}}, equivalent to {{suffix|heave|y|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{m|sco|hevy}}, {{m|sco|havy}}, {{m|sco|heavy||heavy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{m|nl|hevig||violent, severe, intense, acute}}, {{etyl|gml|-}} {{m|gml|hēvich||violent, fierce, intense}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|de|hebig}} (compare {{m|de|heftig||fierce, severe, intense, violent, heavy}}), {{etyl|is|-}} {{m|is|höfugur||heavy, weighty, important}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{m|la|capāx||large, wide, roomy, spacious, capacious, capable, apt}}.

